  {
    "id": "f_csv_90b6607c7c",
    "slug": "i-thought-that-exile-meant-you-had-to-leave-your-country-and-you-could-go-anywhe",
    "texto": "I thought that exile meant you had to leave your country and you could go anywhere--somewhere in the sun, a tropical island, say, or America. But exile doesn't mean that; it means you are banished to a specific place, and guess what, that place isn't in the sun and is no paradise, it's not even America. It's some cold, miserable place like Siberia, where you don't know anyone and you can barely survive. It's another prison.",
